fast any day of the week.","This recipe makes approx. 1000 g of marmalade. Transferred into airtight storage jars, it will make ideal gifts for family and friends.","Reduce temperature to 90°C halfway through cooking time if marmalade begins to bubble onto mixing bowl lid.","Adjust sugar content according to the tartness of your fruit and your personal taste preference.","<b>Setting point test<b>: place a saucer into the freezer (5-10 minutes). Place 1 tsp marmalade onto the chilled saucer. When marmalade on saucer is cool, push it with your finger. If the marmalade wrinkles, it is ready. If not, cook marmalade for a further 2 minutes then test again.","For a different texture to your marmalade, you may want to julienne (finely slice) your citrus zest instead of grating in step 1.","If a thicker consistency is desired, use jam setter or natural pectin obtainable from health food stores."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","2h 20m","1 litre"]}